Hey! Just a heads up. The `restart_child/1` is not restarting a running process. This tests succeeds because the `Server` is not restarted. To test for a successful restart you can do:

```
assert :ok == Supervisor.restart_child(Todo.Supervisor, Server)
```

Because json properties can be null, json schema classes require many nullable annotations.
And, these annotations do not help reduce NRE.
So I decide to disable annotations.

In many cases, --including MicroBatchFramework.Tests--, `Context` is used without checking if it is `null`.
So annotate that `Context` is non-null.
